race.comment: THEY'REALLSISTERS (7) jumped favourite on debut here over 1100m when unable to reel in the leader from midfield. Track pattern probably didn't favour her there, but she closed off strongly and the rise in trip looks ideal. Can go one better this time around. OPTIMUS PRIME (3) finished off nicely on debut and this looks to shape similarly. May be able to sit a little closer going up in trip slightly and he can improve on what he did on debut. Can make his presence felt. BOY CRUSH (1) meets his rivals worse at the weights today following a strong victory over 1100m on debut, beating a lot of this field. Maps to get the run of the race once again and there's no reason why he can't repeat the dose. SOVEREIGN ROCK (2) can set the tempo as he did at Pinjarra last start and be in this for a very long way. LONDON ROSE (5) has trialled nicely since her last run 77 days ago and the rise in trip can see her in the finish.
